## v2.0.0 - Apr 9, 2024

Migrate to Phaser Editor v4.

children.name: README.md
children.content:
# Sunny Land, a Phaser Editor example game

This is a port to Phaser 3 of the [Sunny Land demo made by Luis Zuno](https://ansimuz.itch.io/sunny-land-pixel-game-art).

This is a good example of how to use the Tilemap support in the Scene Editor, the User Components and the Animations Editor.

## Configuration

* It is coded in JavaScript.

## Script Nodes

Script nodes are logic objects. You can add a script node to the scene or a game object, for extending it with custom data and behavior.

This project includes the script libraries:

- [@phaserjs/editor-scripts-core](https://github.com/phaserjs/editor-scripts-core)

children.name: index.html
children.content:
<html lang="en">

<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
	<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">

	<title>Sunny Land (Phaser Editor 2D port)</title>

	<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/phaser@v3.80.1/dist/phaser.min.js"></script>

	<!-- script nodes -->
	<script src="./phaserjs_editor_scripts_core/lib/phaserjs_editor_scripts_core.js"></script>

	<!-- user components -->
	<script src="src/components/CharacterMoveComp.js"></script>
	<script src="src/components/ControllerButtonComp.js"></script>
	<script src="src/components/FixedToCameraComp.js"></script>
	<script src="src/components/StartAnimationComp.js"></script>

	<!-- prefabs -->
	<script src="src/prefabs/Cherry.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/Eagle.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/EnemyDeath.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/FeedbackItem.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/Frog.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/Gem.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/Opossum.js"></script>
	<script src="src/prefabs/Player.js"></script>

	<!-- scenes -->
	<script src="src/scenes/Preloader.js"></script>
	<script src="src/scenes/TitleScreen.js"></script>
	<script src="src/scenes/Level.js"></script>

	<!-- main -->
	<script src="src/main.js"></script>

	<style>
		body {
			background: black;
			margin: 0;
			padding: 0;
		}
	</style>

</head>

<body>
</body>

</html>
